[6.091, "o", "\r\n🤖 [@trinity]\r\nUnderstood. This is a complex task involving video generation. Following the Trinity Orchestration Protocol, I will now delegate the planning phase to the Architect to design the `render.sh` script.\r\n\r\n@architect, please create a bash script named `render.sh` that takes an image (`/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.png`) and an audio file (`/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.wav`) as input. The script should produce an MP4 video (`output.mp4`) with the following specifications:\r\n\r\n*   **Resolution**: 1080x1920 pixels (portrait, suitable for YouTube Shorts).\r\n*   **Image Scaling/Cropping**: The input image must be scaled and cropped to perfectly fit the 1080x1920 resolution, covering the entire frame without any letterboxing.\r\n*   **Video Duration**: The total video duration must precisely match the exact full duration of the input audio.\r\n*   **Audio Encoding**: The audio stream should be encoded using an optimal profil"]
[0.000, "o", "e for YouTube, typically AAC with a bitrate between 128kbps and 192kbps, a sample rate of 44.1kHz, and stereo channels.\r\n\r\nOnce the script is created, I will proceed with its execution and validation.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "[System] Handoff to @architect detected.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Thinking (@architect)...\r\n"]
[30.449, "o", "\r\n🤖 [@architect]\r\nAlright, @trinity, I have analyzed the requirements and designed the `render.sh` script. The plan focuses on utilizing FFmpeg to achieve the specified video characteristics, including precise image scaling and cropping to fill the frame, exact audio-driven duration, and YouTube-optimized audio/video encoding.\r\n\r\nHere is the detailed plan and the `render.sh` script:\r\n\r\n**Plan Breakdown:**\r\n1.  **Input/Output Paths**: Define variables for the input image (`/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.png`), input audio (`/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.wav`), and the output video (`./output.mp4`).\r\n2.  **Audio Duration Extraction**: Use `ffprobe` to accurately determine the duration of the input audio file. This duration will dictate the total length of the generated video.\r\n3.  **Video Stream Generation**: The input image will be looped for the determined audio duration.\r\n4.  **Image Scaling and Cropping (Fill Mode)**: A comp"]
[0.000, "o", "lex FFmpeg `scale` and `crop` filter chain will be used to ensure the image scales to cover the entire 1080x1920 frame while maintaining its aspect ratio. The logic `scale='iw*max(1080/iw,1920/ih)':ih*max(1080/iw,1920/ih)',crop=1080:1920:(ow-1080)/2:(oh-1920)/2` ensures the image is scaled to a size where both its dimensions are at least as large as the target (1080x1920) relative to its original aspect ratio, then it's center-cropped to the exact target resolution.\r\n5.  **Video Encoding**: H.264 codec (`libx264`) will be used with a `medium` preset for a good balance of quality and encoding speed. The pixel format will be `yuv420p` for broad compatibility, and the framerate will be set to 30 FPS with appropriate GOP settings for YouTube.\r\n6.  **Audio Encoding**: The audio will be encoded using the AAC codec (`aac`) with a bitrate of 192kbps, a sample rate of 44.1kHz, and stereo channels (`ac 2`), which are optimal settings for YouTube.\r\n7.  **Stream Mapping**: Explicitly map the video stream from the image i"]
[0.000, "o", "nput and the audio stream from the audio input to prevent unexpected behavior.\r\n8.  **Error Handling**: The script includes basic error checking for `ffprobe` to ensure the audio duration is successfully retrieved.\r\n\r\n**File:** `render.sh`\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\n\r\n# Define input and output file paths\r\nIMAGE_PATH=\"/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.png\"\r\nAUDIO_PATH=\"/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.wav\"\r\nOUTPUT_PATH=\"./output.mp4\" # Output to current directory\r\n\r\n# Target video resolution\r\nTARGET_WIDTH=1080\r\nTARGET_HEIGHT=1920\r\n\r\n# Get audio duration using ffprobe\r\nAUDIO_DURATION=$(ffprobe -v error -show_entries format=duration -of default=noprint_wrappers=1:nokey=1 \"$AUDIO_PATH\")\r\n\r\nif [ -z \"$AUDIO_DURATION\" ]; then\r\n  echo \"Error: Could not determine audio duration from $AUDIO_PATH. Exiting.\"\r\n  exit 1\r\nfi\r\n\r\necho \"Audio duration: $AUDIO_DURATION seconds\"\r\necho \"Generating video...\"\r\n\r\n# FFmpeg command to generate the video\r\n# -loop "]
[0.000, "o", "1: Loop the image indefinitely\r\n# -i \"$IMAGE_PATH\": Input image\r\n# -i \"$AUDIO_PATH\": Input audio\r\n# -t \"$AUDIO_DURATION\": Set video duration to match audio duration\r\n# -c:v libx264: Video codec H.264\r\n# -pix_fmt yuv420p: Pixel format for broad compatibility (e.g., for older devices/players)\r\n# -vf: Video filter graph\r\n#   scale='iw*max($TARGET_WIDTH/iw,$TARGET_HEIGHT/ih)':ih*max($TARGET_WIDTH/iw,$TARGET_HEIGHT/ih)': Scale image to fill the target resolution, maintaining aspect ratio.\r\n#   crop=$TARGET_WIDTH:$TARGET_HEIGHT:(ow-$TARGET_WIDTH)/2:(oh-$TARGET_HEIGHT)/2: Center crop to the target resolution.\r\n#   format=yuv420p: Ensure pixel format again after scaling/cropping for consistency.\r\n# -preset medium: H.264 encoding preset (medium offers good balance of speed and quality)\r\n# -r 30: Set framerate to 30 FPS\r\n# -g 30 -keyint_min 30: Set GOP size and min keyframe interval (GOP of 30 frames for 30 FPS provides good seeking responsiveness)\r\n# -c:a aac: Audio codec AAC\r\n# -b:a 192k: Audio bitrate 192 kbps (opti"]
[0.000, "o", "mal for YouTube, good quality)\r\n# -ar 44100: Audio sample rate 44.1 kHz\r\n# -ac 2: Stereo audio channels\r\n# -map 0:v:0: Map video stream from first input (image)\r\n# -map 1:a:0: Map audio stream from second input (audio file)\r\n# -y: Overwrite output file if it exists\r\nffmpeg \\\r\n  -loop 1 \\\r\n  -i \"$IMAGE_PATH\" \\\r\n  -i \"$AUDIO_PATH\" \\\r\n  -t \"$AUDIO_DURATION\" \\\r\n  -c:v libx264 \\\r\n  -pix_fmt yuv420p \\\r\n  -vf \"scale='iw*max($TARGET_WIDTH/iw,$TARGET_HEIGHT/ih)':ih*max($TARGET_WIDTH/iw,$TARGET_HEIGHT/ih)',crop=$TARGET_WIDTH:$TARGET_HEIGHT:(ow-$TARGET_WIDTH)/2:(oh-$TARGET_HEIGHT)/2,format=yuv420p\" \\\r\n  -preset medium \\\r\n  -r 30 \\\r\n  -g 30 \\\r\n  -keyint_min 30 \\\r\n  -c:a aac \\\r\n  -b:a 192k \\\r\n  -ar 44100 \\\r\n  -ac 2 \\\r\n  -map 0:v:0 \\\r\n  -map 1:a:0 \\\r\n  -y \"$OUTPUT_PATH\"\r\n\r\nif [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\r\n  echo \"Video generated successfully: $OUTPUT_PATH\"\r\nelse\r\n  echo \"Error: Video generation failed.\"\r\n  exit 1\r\nfi\r\n```\r\n\r\n@coder, please implement this `render.sh` script to generate the video as planned.\r\n\r\n"]
