[12.653, "o", "\r\n🤖 [@coder]\r\nI have strictly followed the Architect's plan and generated the `render.sh` script. The script is designed to create a YouTube Shorts MP4 video (1080x1920) by scaling and cropping the input image to fit, matching the exact full duration of the audio, and using YouTube-optimal audio/video profiles.\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\n\r\n# Define input and output file paths\r\nIMAGE_PATH=\"/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.png\"\r\nAUDIO_PATH=\"/Users/stepants/dev/cognitive-resonance/docs/assets/trinity-demo-input.wav\"\r\nOUTPUT_PATH=\"./output.mp4\" # Output to current directory\r\n\r\n# Target video resolution\r\nTARGET_WIDTH=1080\r\nTARGET_HEIGHT=1920\r\n\r\n# Get audio duration using ffprobe\r\nAUDIO_DURATION=$(ffprobe -v error -show_entries format=duration -of default=noprint_wrappers=1:nokey=1 \"$AUDIO_PATH\")\r\n\r\nif [ -z \"$AUDIO_DURATION\" ]; then\r\n  echo \"Error: Could not determine audio duration from $AUDIO_PATH. Exiting.\"\r\n  exit 1\r\nfi\r\n\r\necho \"Audio duration: $AUDIO_DURATION seconds\"\r\nec"]
[0.000, "o", "ho \"Generating video...\"\r\n\r\n# FFmpeg command to generate the video\r\n# -loop 1: Loop the image indefinitely\r\n# -i \"$IMAGE_PATH\": Input image\r\n# -i \"$AUDIO_PATH\": Input audio\r\n# -t \"$AUDIO_DURATION\": Set video duration to match audio duration\r\n# -c:v libx264: Video codec H.264\r\n# -pix_fmt yuv420p: Pixel format for broad compatibility (e.g., for older devices/players)\r\n# -vf: Video filter graph\r\n#   scale='iw*max($TARGET_WIDTH/iw,$TARGET_HEIGHT/ih)':ih*max($TARGET_WIDTH/iw,$TARGET_HEIGHT/ih)': Scale image to fill the target resolution, maintaining aspect ratio.\r\n#   crop=$TARGET_WIDTH:$TARGET_HEIGHT:(ow-$TARGET_WIDTH)/2:(oh-$TARGET_HEIGHT)/2: Center crop to the target resolution.\r\n#   format=yuv420p: Ensure pixel format again after scaling/cropping for consistency.\r\n# -preset medium: H.264 encoding preset (medium offers good balance of speed and quality)\r\n# -r 30: Set framerate to 30 FPS\r\n# -g 30 -keyint_min 30: Set GOP size and min keyframe interval (GOP of 30 frames for 30 FPS provides good seeking responsiven"]
[0.000, "o", "ess)\r\n# -c:a aac: Audio codec AAC\r\n# -b:a 192k: Audio bitrate 192 kbps (optimal for YouTube, good quality)\r\n# -ar 44100: Audio sample rate 44.1 kHz\r\n# -ac 2: Stereo audio channels\r\n# -map 0:v:0: Map video stream from first input (image)\r\n# -map 1:a:0: Map audio stream from second input (audio file)\r\n# -y: Overwrite output file if it exists\r\nffmpeg \\\r\n  -loop 1 \\\r\n  -i \"$IMAGE_PATH\" \\\r\n  -i \"$AUDIO_PATH\" \\\r\n  -t \"$AUDIO_DURATION\" \\\r\n  -c:v libx264 \\\r\n  -pix_fmt yuv420p \\\r\n  -vf \"scale='iw*max($TARGET_WIDTH/iw,$TARGET_HEIGHT/ih)':ih*max($TARGET_WIDTH/iw,$TARGET_HEIGHT/ih)',crop=$TARGET_WIDTH:$TARGET_HEIGHT:(ow-$TARGET_WIDTH)/2:(oh-$TARGET_HEIGHT)/2,format=yuv420p\" \\\r\n  -preset medium \\\r\n  -r 30 \\\r\n  -g 30 \\\r\n  -keyint_min 30 \\\r\n  -c:a aac \\\r\n  -b:a 192k \\\r\n  -ar 44100 \\\r\n  -ac 2 \\\r\n  -map 0:v:0 \\\r\n  -map 1:a:0 \\\r\n  -y \"$OUTPUT_PATH\"\r\n\r\nif [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\r\n  echo \"Video generated successfully: $OUTPUT_PATH\"\r\nelse\r\n  echo \"Error: Video generation failed.\"\r\n  exit 1\r\nfi\r\n```\r\n\r\n@auditor, please review this code"]
